post_cb({"25709653": {"ViewCount": "121", "Body": "<p>I have the following minimal example:</p>\n<pre><code>class A\n{\n  template&lt;typename X, typename Y&gt;\n  void f()\n  { }\n\n  template&lt;&gt;\n  void f&lt;int, char&gt;()\n  { }\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>The compiler gives an error message </p>\n<pre><code> explicit specialzation in non-namespace scope.\n</code></pre>\n<p>Why is this wrong and how can I fix it?</p>\n", "Title": "Explicit template specialization of member functions", "CreationDate": "2014-09-07T11:22:43.023", "Id": "25709653", "CommentCount": "2", "LastEditDate": "2014-09-07T11:26:13.823", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "1413395", "LastActivityDate": "2014-09-07T11:29:24.157", "Tags": "<c++><templates>", "Score": "3", "OwnerUserId": "2683038", "ClosedDate": "2014-09-07T11:29:23.877", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_25709653_25709686_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 264}, "so_25709653_25709691_0": {"length": 18, "quality": 0.5806451612903226, "section_id": 150}}, "n3337": {"so_25709653_25709686_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 255}, "so_25709653_25709691_0": {"length": 18, "quality": 0.5806451612903226, "section_id": 144}}, "n4659": {"so_25709653_25709686_0": {"length": 6, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "section_id": 285}, "so_25709653_25709691_0": {"length": 18, "quality": 0.5806451612903226, "section_id": 154}}}, "25709686": {"Id": "25709686", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>\u00a714.7.3 [temp.expl.spec]/p2:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_25709653_25709686_0\">An explicit specialization shall be declared in a namespace enclosing the specialized template.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So you need to move the specialization outside <code>A</code>'s definition:</p>\n<pre><code>class A\n{\n  template&lt;typename X, typename Y&gt;\n  void f()\n  { }\n};\n\ntemplate&lt;&gt;\nvoid A::f&lt;int, char&gt;()\n{ }\n</code></pre>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2014-09-07T11:28:22.140", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2014-09-07T11:28:22.140", "ParentId": "25709653", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "2756719"}, "25709691": {"Id": "25709691", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>From the C++ standards:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_25709653_25709691_0\">An explicit specialization shall be declared in the namespace of which\n  the template is a member, or, for member templates, in the namespace\n  of which the enclosing class or enclosing class template is a member.\n  An explicit specialization of a member function, member class or\n  static data member of a class template shall be declared in the\n  namespace of which the class template is a member.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So you need to move the specialization outside  the scope of A's definition. You may try this:</p>\n<pre><code>class A\n{\n  template&lt;typename X, typename Y&gt;\n  void f()\n  { }\n};\ntemplate&lt;&gt;\nvoid A::f&lt;int, char&gt;()\n{ }\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerDisplayName": "user3414693", "LastEditorUserId": "1501794", "LastActivityDate": "2014-09-07T11:29:24.157", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2014-09-07T11:29:24.157", "ParentId": "25709653", "CommentCount": "2", "OwnerUserId": "1501794"}});